# OOP

Object oriented programming is very powerful, and nowadays, it is the standard.

Classes are useful to organize the code.

```python
# Curriculum Vitae Arthur GOSSUIN

class ArthurGossuin:
    """Passionate Coder"""

    def __init__(self):
        self.name = 'Arthur'
        self.surname = 'Gossuin'
        self.age = 26
        self.phone_number = '+32 470 05 54 30'
        self.email_address = 'arthur.gossuin@gmail.com'
        self.github_profile = 'https://github.com/Artygo8'
        self.living_place = 'Chauss√©e de Wavre 1410, 1180 Brussels'
        self.current_activity = 'Software Engineer at Odoo'
        self.interests = ['code', 'music', 'technology', 'education']

    def become_geologist(self):
        print(self.name, 'has a BA in Geology from the ULB!')

    def become_coder(self):
        print(f'{self.name} loves to code!'.title())

    def study(self):
        # self.become_civil_engineer()
        self.become_geologist()
        # self.become_sound_engineer()
        self.become_coder()

    def get_hired(self):
        answer = input('Do you want to hire me? ').lower()
        print('Hoorray!' if 'ye' in answer else 'Ooooh...')


if __name__ == '__main__':
    me = ArthurGossuin()
    me.study()
    me.get_hired()
```
